                <h3>What is Kishori Vikas Prakalp?</h3>
                <p>
                    <strong>'Kishori Vikas Prakalp'</strong> is an initiative by <b>Vasundhara Sanjivani Mandal Thane, Maharashtra</b> for the teenage girls in <i>Shahapur</i> and <i>Murbad</i> Talukas. 
                    The age group for these teenage girls is 12 years to 18 years.
                </p>
                <h3>What is the need of Kishori Vikas Prakalp?</h3>
                <p>
                    The idea for Kishori Vikas Prakalp was founded while working with the girls.
                    The need for Kishori Vikas Prakalp due to following reasons,
                    <ul>
                        <li>Changed lifestyle in society</li>
                        <li>Family system</li>
                        <li>Excessive flow of information through society</li>
                        <li>Perspective towards women</li>
                        <li>Issues of adolescents</li>
                        <li>Decreasing communication between parents and children</li>
                    </ul>
                </p>

                <h3>Vision of Kishori Vikas Prakalp</h3>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Helping adolescent girls to express their thoughts and develop a sense of independent personality.</li>
                        <li>Assisting them in making the right choices and solving their problems on their own to make decisions independently.</li>
                        <li>Providing appropriate help to boost their confidence and enhance their personality.</li>
                        <li>Encouraging girls by nurturing their latent talents with professional information and artistic skills.</li>
                        <li>Promoting their resilience, thinking, and expression abilities.</li>
                    </ul>                      
                </p>

                <h3>Activities conducted at Kishori Vikas Prakalp</h3>
                <p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Sessions based on motivational songs, heroic women, games, health, nutrition, personality development, and sex education</li>
                        <li>Open discussions and intellectual debates prove useful for girls in their daily lives</li>
                        <li>Adolescent classes have started in urban as well as rural schools and communities</li>
                        <li>These classes are held for one hour a week, totaling four hours a month</li>
                        <li>The girls participating in this initiative will benefit from it</li>
                    </ul>                      
                </p>
            </div>

